==English==
===Alternate forms===
:'''contourny'''

===Etymology===
From {{L.}} ''[[con-]]'' "altogether, completely" and [[tornare|tornāre]] "to make round".

===Adjective===
'''contourné'''
#(''heraldry'') In [[blazon]], a term used to describe beasts or monsters that have been turned around to face [[sinister]] instead of [[dexter]].

